34#define INITIAL_BUFFER_SIZE 1024
35#define BUFFER_EXTRA 1024
36
37#define REGION_TO_GBUFFER(r, gb) \
38 do { \
39 (gb).length = (r).length; \
40 (gb).value = (r).base; \
41 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
42
43#define GBUFFER_TO_REGION(gb, r) \
44 do { \
45 (r).length = (unsigned int)(gb).length; \
46 (r).base = (gb).value; \
47 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
48
49
50struct dst_gssapi_signverifyctx {
51 isc_buffer_t *buffer;
52};
53
54/*%
55 * Allocate a temporary "context" for use in gathering data for signing
56 * or verifying.
57 */
58static isc_result_t
59gssapi_create_signverify_ctx(dst_key_t *key, dst_context_t *dctx) {
60 dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t *ctx;
61 isc_result_t result;
62
63 UNUSED(key);
64
65 ctx = isc_mem_get(dctx->mctx, sizeof(dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t));
66 if (ctx == NULL)
67 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
68 ctx->buffer = NULL;
69 result = isc_buffer_allocate(dctx->mctx, &ctx->buffer,
70 INITIAL_BUFFER_SIZE);
71 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
72 isc_mem_put(dctx->mctx, ctx, sizeof(dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t));
73 return (result);
74 }
75
76 dctx->ctxdata.gssctx = ctx;
77
78 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
79}
80
81/*%
82 * Destroy the temporary sign/verify context.
83 */
84static void
85gssapi_destroy_signverify_ctx(dst_context_t *dctx) {
86 dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t *ctx = dctx->ctxdata.gssctx;
87
88 if (ctx != NULL) {
89 if (ctx->buffer != NULL)
90 isc_buffer_free(&ctx->buffer);
91 isc_mem_put(dctx->mctx, ctx, sizeof(dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t));
92 dctx->ctxdata.gssctx = NULL;
93 }
94}
95
96/*%
97 * Add data to our running buffer of data we will be signing or verifying.
98 * This code will see if the new data will fit in our existing buffer, and
99 * copy it in if it will. If not, it will attempt to allocate a larger
100 * buffer and copy old+new into it, and free the old buffer.
101 */
102static isc_result_t
103gssapi_adddata(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *data) {
104 dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t *ctx = dctx->ctxdata.gssctx;
105 isc_buffer_t *newbuffer = NULL;
106 isc_region_t r;
107 unsigned int length;
108 isc_result_t result;
109
110 result = isc_buffer_copyregion(ctx->buffer, data);
111 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
112 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
113
114 length = isc_buffer_length(ctx->buffer) + data->length + BUFFER_EXTRA;
115
116 result = isc_buffer_allocate(dctx->mctx, &newbuffer, length);
117 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
118 return (result);
119
120 isc_buffer_usedregion(ctx->buffer, &r);
121 (void)isc_buffer_copyregion(newbuffer, &r);
122 (void)isc_buffer_copyregion(newbuffer, data);
123
124 isc_buffer_free(&ctx->buffer);
125 ctx->buffer = newbuffer;
126
127 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
128}
129
130/*%
131 * Sign.
132 */
133static isc_result_t
134gssapi_sign(dst_context_t *dctx, isc_buffer_t *sig) {
135 dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t *ctx = dctx->ctxdata.gssctx;
136 isc_region_t message;
137 gss_buffer_desc gmessage, gsig;
138 OM_uint32 minor, gret;
139 gss_ctx_id_t gssctx = dctx->key->keydata.gssctx;
140 char buf[1024];
141
142 /*
143 * Convert the data we wish to sign into a structure gssapi can
144 * understand.
145 */
146 isc_buffer_usedregion(ctx->buffer, &message);
147 REGION_TO_GBUFFER(message, gmessage);
148
149 /*
150 * Generate the signature.
151 */
152 gret = gss_get_mic(&minor, gssctx, GSS_C_QOP_DEFAULT, &gmessage,
153 &gsig);
154
155 /*
156 * If it did not complete, we log the result and return a generic
157 * failure code.
158 */
159 if (gret != GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
160 gss_log(3, "GSS sign error: %s",
161 gss_error_tostring(gret, minor, buf, sizeof(buf)));
162 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
163 }
164
165 /*
166 * If it will not fit in our allocated buffer, return that we need
167 * more space.
168 */
169 if (gsig.length > isc_buffer_availablelength(sig)) {
170 gss_release_buffer(&minor, &gsig);
171 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
172 }
173
174 /*
175 * Copy the output into our buffer space, and release the gssapi
176 * allocated space.
177 */
178 isc_buffer_putmem(sig, gsig.value, (unsigned int)gsig.length);
179 if (gsig.length != 0U)
180 gss_release_buffer(&minor, &gsig);
181
182 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
183}
184
185/*%
186 * Verify.
187 */
188static isc_result_t
189gssapi_verify(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *sig) {
190 dst_gssapi_signverifyctx_t *ctx = dctx->ctxdata.gssctx;
191 isc_region_t message, r;
192 gss_buffer_desc gmessage, gsig;
193 OM_uint32 minor, gret;
194 gss_ctx_id_t gssctx = dctx->key->keydata.gssctx;
195 unsigned char buf[4096];
196 char err[1024];
197
198 if (sizeof(buf) < sig->length)
199 abort();
200
201 /*
202 * Convert the data we wish to sign into a structure gssapi can
203 * understand.
204 */
205 isc_buffer_usedregion(ctx->buffer, &message);
206 REGION_TO_GBUFFER(message, gmessage);
207
208 memmove(buf, sig->base, sig->length);
209 r.base = buf;
210 r.length = sig->length;
211 REGION_TO_GBUFFER(r, gsig);
212
213 /*
214 * Verify the data.
215 */
216 gret = gss_verify_mic(&minor, gssctx, &gmessage, &gsig, NULL);
217
218 /*
219 * Convert return codes into something useful to us.
220 */
221 if (gret != GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
222 gss_log(3, "GSS verify error: %s",
223 gss_error_tostring(gret, minor, err, sizeof(err)));
224 if (gret == GSS_S_DEFECTIVE_TOKEN ||
225 gret == GSS_S_BAD_SIG ||
226 gret == GSS_S_DUPLICATE_TOKEN ||
227 gret == GSS_S_OLD_TOKEN ||
228 gret == GSS_S_UNSEQ_TOKEN ||
229 gret == GSS_S_GAP_TOKEN ||
230 gret == GSS_S_CONTEXT_EXPIRED ||
231 gret == GSS_S_NO_CONTEXT ||
232 gret == GSS_S_FAILURE)
233 return(DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE);
234 else
235 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
236 }
237
238 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
239}

241static bool
242gssapi_compare(const dst_key_t *key1, const dst_key_t *key2) {
243 gss_ctx_id_t gsskey1 = key1->keydata.gssctx;
244 gss_ctx_id_t gsskey2 = key2->keydata.gssctx;
245
246 /* No idea */
247 return (gsskey1 == gsskey2);
248}

250static isc_result_t
251gssapi_generate(dst_key_t *key, int unused, void (*callback)(int)) {
252 UNUSED(key);
253 UNUSED(unused);
254 UNUSED(callback);
255
256 /* No idea */
257 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
258}

260static bool
261gssapi_isprivate(const dst_key_t *key) {
262 UNUSED(key);
263 return (true);
264}

266static void
267gssapi_destroy(dst_key_t *key) {
268 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
269 dst_gssapi_deletectx(key->mctx, &key->keydata.gssctx);
270 key->keydata.gssctx = NULL;
271}
272
273static isc_result_t
274gssapi_restore(dst_key_t *key, const char *keystr) {
275 OM_uint32 major, minor;
276 unsigned int len;
277 isc_buffer_t *b = NULL;
278 isc_region_t r;
279 gss_buffer_desc gssbuffer;
280 isc_result_t result;
281
282 len = strlen(keystr);
283 if ((len % 4) != 0U)
284 return (ISC_R_BADBASE64);
285
286 len = (len / 4) * 3;
287
288 result = isc_buffer_allocate(key->mctx, &b, len);
289 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
290 return (result);
291
292 result = isc_base64_decodestring(keystr, b);
293 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
294 isc_buffer_free(&b);
295 return (result);
296 }
297
298 isc_buffer_remainingregion(b, &r);
299 REGION_TO_GBUFFER(r, gssbuffer);
300 major = gss_import_sec_context(&minor, &gssbuffer,
301 &key->keydata.gssctx);
302 if (major != GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
303 isc_buffer_free(&b);
304 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
305 }
306
307 isc_buffer_free(&b);
308 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
309}
310
311static isc_result_t
312gssapi_dump(dst_key_t *key, isc_mem_t *mctx, char **buffer, int *length) {
313 OM_uint32 major, minor;
314 gss_buffer_desc gssbuffer;
315 size_t len;
316 char *buf;
317 isc_buffer_t b;
318 isc_region_t r;
319 isc_result_t result;
320
321 major = gss_export_sec_context(&minor, &key->keydata.gssctx,
322 &gssbuffer);
323 if (major != GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
324 fprintf(stderr, "gss_export_sec_context -> %d, %d\n",
325 major, minor);
326 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
327 }
328 if (gssbuffer.length == 0U)
329 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
330 len = ((gssbuffer.length + 2)/3) * 4;
331 buf = isc_mem_get(mctx, len);
332 if (buf == NULL) {
333 gss_release_buffer(&minor, &gssbuffer);
334 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
335 }
336 isc_buffer_init(&b, buf, (unsigned int)len);
337 GBUFFER_TO_REGION(gssbuffer, r);
338 result = isc_base64_totext(&r, 0, "", &b);
339 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
340 gss_release_buffer(&minor, &gssbuffer);
341 *buffer = buf;
342 *length = (int)len;
343 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
344}

346static dst_func_t gssapi_functions = {
347 gssapi_create_signverify_ctx,
348 NULL, /*%< createctx2 */
349 gssapi_destroy_signverify_ctx,
350 gssapi_adddata,
351 gssapi_sign,
352 gssapi_verify,
353 NULL, /*%< verify2 */
354 NULL, /*%< computesecret */
355 gssapi_compare,
356 NULL, /*%< paramcompare */
357 gssapi_generate,
358 gssapi_isprivate,
359 gssapi_destroy,
360 NULL, /*%< todns */
361 NULL, /*%< fromdns */
362 NULL, /*%< tofile */
363 NULL, /*%< parse */
364 NULL, /*%< cleanup */
365 NULL, /*%< fromlabel */
366 gssapi_dump,
367 gssapi_restore,
368};
369
370isc_result_t
371dst__gssapi_init(dst_func_t **funcp) {
372 REQUIRE(funcp != NULL);
373 if (*funcp == NULL)
374 *funcp = &gssapi_functions;
375 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
376}
